  "translations": {
    "en": {
      "description": {
        "text": "Adjacent to the mountain in Sulvik, there are several bouldering problems. This is their guide.\n\nThis guide can be found and is most up-to-date at http://27crags.com/crags/sulvik (http://27crags.com/crags/sulvik).",
        "method": "llm",
        "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
        "sourceIds": [
          "legacy:sulvik-boulder"
        ]
      },
      "sections": {
        "allmant": {
          "title": {
            "text": "General",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:sulvik-boulder"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "Directly adjacent to the mountain in Sulvik, there are several bouldering problems. This is its guide.\n\nThis guide can be found and is most current at http://27crags.com/crags/sulvik (http://27crags.com/crags/sulvik).",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:sulvik-boulder"
            ]
          }
        },
        "vagbeskrivning": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Directions",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:sulvik-boulder"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "From Arvika: Follow road 172 towards Årjäng/Töcksfors/Sulvik. After passing Sulvik with its petrol station/convenience store, take the first road on the right towards Åmotfors. After about a kilometre, you'll find Kolsjön on your left, which indicates you've gone a bit too far. Instead, park your car at the meadow on the right. The mountain is at the other end of the small field (200m) and the beginning of the mountain should be visible from the car. If the field is being cultivated, the vehicle must be parked higher up the hill where there is a small pull-in. From there, it's a walk across the clear-cut area.\n\nAccess: At the meadow, there's only a parking pull-in, a bit off the road; never use the road/meadow. All other areas are used by the landowner. Preferably park up on the crest beforehand, or continue driving and park in the sharp bend on the side road. Please respect the landowner's needs.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:sulvik-boulder"
            ]
          }
        },
        "blockoversikt": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Block Overview",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:sulvik-boulder"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "Here we will list where the different boulders are located with an overview image.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:sulvik-boulder"
            ]
          }
        },
        "vaggproblem": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Wall Problems",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:sulvik-boulder"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "Oscar Wall:",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:sulvik-boulder"
            ]
          }
        },
        "bostadsblocket": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Residential Block",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:sulvik-boulder"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "Information about the Residential Block and its location will eventually be added here.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:sulvik-boulder"
            ]
          }
        },
        "dodsblocket": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Death Block",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:sulvik-boulder"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "After the Residential Block, the lake/swamp starts, and the Death Block is about 40 metres further to the right. The Beavercreek Block is located directly adjacent to the Death Block. There are opportunities for around a dozen projects.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:sulvik-boulder"
            ]
          }
        },
        "lagerplatsblocken": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Campsite Blocks",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:sulvik-boulder"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "Once you enter the forest, you will walk straight towards the blocks; can't miss them.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:sulvik-boulder"
            ]
          }
        },
        "beavercreek-blocket": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Beavercreek Block",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:sulvik-boulder"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "Different sides have different characteristics. The slightly overhanging side has a very catch-friendly edge and excellent landing. Unfortunately, there are no holds. A handful of projects can be established on the stone.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:sulvik-boulder"
            ]
          }
        },
        "narvaroblocket": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Presence Block",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:sulvik-boulder"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "The block is the furthest away and has the potential for more problems.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:sulvik-boulder"
            ]
          }
        },
        "boulderleder": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Bouldering Routes",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:sulvik-boulder"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "• Gränsleden 6b finger 7m, finger crack, sit start\n• Sulvik in My Heart 6a 6m, sit start\n• Elimination 6b, arete to the right of \"Sulvik in...\"\n• Ekefalk's Problem 7a 10m\n• Why Can't I Finish the Wood 6c (haha) 6m, crux at the end\n• Do You Know Where You Are, Ethen? 6c+",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:sulvik-boulder"
            ]
          }
        }
      },
